@user1:
@author can you explain why the docs build is causing us problems here? Would love to avoid needing `_FIFTYONE_FORCE_DB_CONNECT_ON_IMPORT` if at all possible

@author:
Yeah I really hate it also 😫😫

Basically it is a mongoengine problem.

Autodoc tries to go in and touch every member and inherited member of each class. Which includes a field on the mongoengine document called "objects" which has a getter that requires the db connection 🤬

So it goes in, the connection has not been made, the "objects" getter fails, and then doc build fails.

I tried to play with autodoc settings including to ignore inherited members or specifically skip "objects", but didn't come up with anything that worked.

I'll try to think of other solutions, but brainstorming welcome

@user1:
I see. One way to clean up a bit would be to only call `migrate_database_if_necessary()` inside `establish_db_conn()`.

To limit the number of places that `_FIFTYONE_FORCE_DB_CONNECT_ON_IMPORT` needs to exist.

@user1:
you tried added `exclude-members` [to the conf](https://github.com/voxel51/fiftyone/blob/85339fcecf03978435fed6fd94565d1c63f58dd6/docs/source/conf.py#L73
)? 


```py
autodoc_default_options = {
    ...
    "exclude-members": "objects"
}
```


@author:
Ok perhaps I do not understand sphinx directives like I thought I did, but adding to `conf.py` works where directly to the automodule directive did not.
I thought I had tried that too but oh well glad it works!
